+    # Triton cannot bind E8M0 scale tensors on ANY platform: its dtype
+    # canonicalisation table has no float8_e8m0fnu entry, so the JIT
+    # binder raises KeyError and the C++ runtime terminates the process
+    # (no Python traceback - the engine just aborts). This guard used to
+    # be ROCm/XPU-only on the assumption that CUDA always consumes UE8M0
+    # scales through DeepGEMM before this fallback is reached - FALSE on
+    # Ada (sm_89): there is no family-120 DeepGEMM path, the DS4
+    # attention fp8 block-scaled linear lands HERE, and the e8m0 Bs of a
+    # scale_fmt=ue8m0 checkpoint aborted the engine at first forward.
+    # Decode unconditionally: E8M0 is exponent-only, the fp32 upcast is
+    # exact (2^(byte-127) via exponent-field bitcast), and the cost is a
+    # few thousand elements per call next to the GEMM itself.
+    if As.dtype == torch.float8_e8m0fnu:
+        As = _upcast_e8m0_to_fp32(As).contiguous()
+    if Bs.dtype == torch.float8_e8m0fnu:
+        Bs = _upcast_e8m0_to_fp32(Bs).contiguous()
 
